The paper proposes a model for direct speech-to-text translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the potential impact of the proposed approach on data collection methodology, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.SD (Sound). The proposed model uses deep learning techniques, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper presents experimental results on a small synthetic corpus, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.SD (Sound) as well.
